  "variant": "PT128H -- N89 PS 128x128 output tile (32 warps, 1024 thd/CTA, 16 f32 acc/lane, 4 mma.m16n8k16/warp/K-step) + N149 PHILB Hilbert d2xy CTA-swizzle. Launch grid p x p, p=next_pow2(side), side=N/128; d=ctaid.y*p+ctaid.x; (sw_x,sw_y)=hilbert_d2xy(p,d) unrolled log2(p) rounds (no runtime loop); early-return padding CTAs (sw_x>=side||sw_y>=side). 128x128-tile MMA body byte-identical to N89.",
  "hexa_kernel_family": "sgemm_tile128_hilbert_SxS_grid",
  "cublas_math_mode": "CUBLAS_TENSOR_OP_MATH (HGEMM via cublasGemmEx)",
  "swizzle_pattern": "Hilbert space-filling curve d2xy on 128-tile grid (side=N/128). Launch p x p (p=next_pow2(side)), d2xy(p, ctaid.y*p+ctaid.x), drop padding tiles outside side x side. Bijective over real grid -> bit-exact. d2xy unrolled at gen time.",
  "l2_size_mb": 32,
  "stack_inputs": {
    "N89_PS":   "rfc067_pS_hexa_sgemm_tile128_2026_05_21 128x128 tile NO swizzle: peak 37.07 @ M=1536 ratio 0.557, lost to 64x64 baseline at M<=1536 (1 CTA/SM occupancy collapse, 47 regs). Not measured at M>=4096.",
    "N149_PHILB": "rfc067_philb_hexa_sgemm_hilbert_swizzle_2026_05_22 64x64 + Hilbert: M=4096 0.821, M=5120 0.827, M=6144 0.834, M=8192 0.847 (best large-M ratio in RFC 067 SGEMM line).",
    "N107_PY":  "4-warp 64x64 canonical: 51.65 TFLOPS @ M=1536 ratio 0.777"
  },
  "hypothesis": "N89 found the 128x128 tile lost to 64x64 at M<=1536 due to 1-CTA/SM occupancy collapse. N149 found a Hilbert CTA-swizzle flattened the large-M L2 cliff on the 64x64 tile (M=8192 0.847). PT128H tests if the bigger tile's larger L2-resident working set per CTA + Hilbert visitation order pushes the large-M ratio PAST 0.847. Two-sided: if 128x128+Hilbert beats 64x64+Hilbert at large M, L2-locality changes the tile-size tradeoff; if it still loses, N89's occupancy-collapse finding holds and bigger tile is the wrong knob on RTX 5070.",
